---
import MinimalLayout from '@layouts/MinimalLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '@components/Breadcrumbs.astro';

const breadcrumbs = [
  { label: 'Home', href: '/' },
  { label: 'Privacy Policy' }
];

const title = "Privacy Policy - Kleva";
const description = "Privacy Policy for Kleva AI debt collection platform";
---

<MinimalLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <article class="legal-page">
    <div class="container">
      <Breadcrumbs items={breadcrumbs} />
      
      <header class="page-header">
        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="last-updated">Last updated: November 2024</p>
      </header>

      <div class="legal-content">
        <section>
          <h2>Introduction</h2>
          <p>
            Kleva, Inc. ("Kleva", "we", "us", or "our") is committed to protecting the 
            privacy and security of personal information. This Privacy Policy describes 
            how we collect, use, disclose, and protect information when you use our 
            AI-powered debt collection platform.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
          
          <h3>1.1 Information from Financial Institutions</h3>
          <p>We process the following data on behalf of our clients:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Debtor contact information (name, phone, email)</li>
            <li>Account details (account numbers, balances, payment history)</li>
            <li>Transaction records</li>
            <li>Communication preferences</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>1.2 Information from Platform Users</h3>
          <p>We collect from users of our platform:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Account registration information</li>
            <li>Login credentials</li>
            <li>Usage data and analytics</li>
            <li>Support requests and communications</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>1.3 Automatically Collected Information</h3>
          <p>Our systems automatically collect:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>IP addresses and device information</li>
            <li>Browser type and version</li>
            <li>Access times and dates</li>
            <li>Platform interaction data</li>
            <li>Call recordings and transcriptions</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>2. How We Use Information</h2>
          <p>We use collected information to:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Provide and operate the debt collection Service</li>
            <li>Contact debtors on behalf of our clients</li>
            <li>Generate reports and analytics</li>
            <li>Improve our AI models and Service quality</li>
            <li>Ensure compliance with regulations</li>
            <li>Provide customer support</li>
            <li>Detect and prevent fraud</li>
            <li>Fulfill legal obligations</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>3. Legal Basis for Processing</h2>
          <p>We process personal data based on:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Legitimate interests:</strong> Operating our business and providing services</li>
            <li><strong>Contract performance:</strong> Fulfilling our agreements with clients</li>
            <li><strong>Legal obligations:</strong> Complying with applicable laws</li>
            <li><strong>Consent:</strong> Where explicitly provided</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>4. Data Sharing and Disclosure</h2>
          <p>We may share information with:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Our clients:</strong> Financial institutions using our Service</li>
            <li><strong>Service providers:</strong> Third parties helping us operate the Service</li>
            <li><strong>Legal authorities:</strong> When required by law or court order</li>
            <li><strong>Business transfers:</strong> In case of merger or acquisition</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            We do not sell personal information to third parties.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>5. International Data Transfers</h2>
          <p>
            Our servers are located in the United States. By using our Service, you 
            consent to the transfer of your information to the United States. We implement 
            appropriate safeguards for international transfers in compliance with applicable laws.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>6. Data Security</h2>
          <p>We implement comprehensive security measures including:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>End-to-end encryption for data transmission</li>
            <li>Encryption at rest for stored data</li>
            <li>Regular security audits and penetration testing</li>
            <li>Access controls and authentication</li>
            <li>Employee training on data protection</li>
            <li>Incident response procedures</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>7. Data Retention</h2>
          <p>
            We retain personal data for as long as necessary to provide our Service and 
            comply with legal obligations. Specific retention periods:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Call recordings: 90 days</li>
            <li>Transaction data: 7 years</li>
            <li>Account information: Duration of service + 3 years</li>
            <li>Analytics data: 2 years</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>8. Your Rights</h2>
          <p>Depending on your location, you may have the right to:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Access:</strong> Request copies of your personal data</li>
            <li><strong>Rectification:</strong> Correct inaccurate information</li>
            <li><strong>Erasure:</strong> Request deletion of your data</li>
            <li><strong>Restriction:</strong> Limit processing of your data</li>
            <li><strong>Portability:</strong> Receive your data in a portable format</li>
            <li><strong>Object:</strong> Oppose certain processing activities</li>
            <li><strong>Withdraw consent:</strong> Where processing is based on consent</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            To exercise these rights, contact us at privacy@kleva.co
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>9. LGPD Compliance (Brazil)</h2>
          <p>
            For Brazilian data subjects, we comply with Lei Geral de Proteção de Dados (LGPD):
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>We process data based on legitimate legal bases</li>
            <li>We appoint a Data Protection Officer</li>
            <li>We conduct privacy impact assessments</li>
            <li>We respect all rights granted under LGPD</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>10. Children's Privacy</h2>
          <p>
            Our Service is not directed to individuals under 18 years of age. We do not 
            knowingly collect personal information from children.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>11. Cookies and Tracking</h2>
          <p>
            We use cookies and similar technologies to:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Maintain user sessions</li>
            <li>Remember preferences</li>
            <li>Analyze platform usage</li>
            <li>Improve Service performance</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            You can control cookies through your browser settings.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>12. AI and Automated Decision-Making</h2>
          <p>
            Our AI systems make automated decisions regarding:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Optimal contact times</li>
            <li>Communication strategies</li>
            <li>Payment plan recommendations</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            Human oversight is always available, and you may request human review of 
            automated decisions.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>13. Changes to This Policy</h2>
          <p>
            We may update this Privacy Policy periodically. We will notify you of material 
            changes via email or platform notification. Continued use after changes 
            constitutes acceptance.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>14. Contact Information</h2>
          <p>
            For privacy-related questions or concerns:
          </p>
          <address>
            Data Protection Officer<br>
            Kleva, Inc.<br>
            Email: privacy@kleva.co<br>
            Phone: +1 704-816-9059<br>
          </address>
          <p>
            You may also contact your local data protection authority if you believe 
            your privacy rights have been violated.
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</MinimalLayout>

<style>
  .legal-page {
    padding: 120px 0 80px;
  }

  .page-header {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto 48px;
    text-align: center;
  }

  h1 {
    font-size: 48px;
    font-weight: 700;
    line-height: 1.2;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    color: var(--color-black);
  }

  .last-updated {
    font-size: 16px;
    color: var(--color-gray-600);
  }

  .legal-content {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .legal-content section {
    margin-bottom: 48px;
  }

  .legal-content h2 {
    font-size: 24px;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    color: var(--color-black);
  }

  .legal-content h3 {
    font-size: 20px;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 24px 0 12px;
    color: var(--color-black);
  }

  .legal-content p {
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    color: var(--color-gray-700);
  }

  .legal-content ul {
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    padding-left: 24px;
  }

  .legal-content li {
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
    color: var(--color-gray-700);
  }

  address {
    font-style: normal;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: var(--color-gray-700);
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    h1 {
      font-size: 32px;
    }

    .legal-content h2 {
      font-size: 20px;
    }

    .legal-content h3 {
      font-size: 18px;
    }
  }
</style>